    <p style="font-size: 13px; color: #888; margin: 0 0 12px; letter-spacing: 0.02em;">
      By <strong>Mitch Chadban</strong> — SEO &amp; Marketing Strategist, Australia | Updated July 2026
    </p>

    <h1>AEO Explained: How to Rank in AI Answers</h1>

    <blockquote>
      <p><strong>Answer Engine Optimisation (AEO)</strong> is the practice of making your content easy for AI answer systems to retrieve, understand, quote and cite. In practical terms, that means publishing pages with direct definitions, clear structure, evidence, useful formatting, and strong technical foundations so platforms like ChatGPT, Gemini, Perplexity and Google AI results are more likely to use your site as a source.</p>
    </blockquote>

    <p>AEO matters because more discovery now happens inside AI-assisted search experiences, not only in traditional search results. If your business publishes useful content but that content is hard to extract, weakly structured, or thin on proof, AI systems are more likely to summarise a competitor instead.</p>

